    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📚 n8n Docs RAG AI Agent\n\nThis workflow:\n1. Scrapes n8n docs from GitHub\n2. Embeds & stores in Supabase\n3. Answers questions via chat\n\n**NEEDED CREDENTIALS:**\n\n🔑 GitHub API\n- Personal Access Token\n\n🔑 Google Gemini (PaLM)\n- API Key\n\n🔑 Supabase API\n- Project URL + Key\n\n🔑 PostgreSQL\n- Connection to same DB as Supabase",
        "height": 576,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -2688,
        -1072
      ],
      "id": "962b6a12-0184-4ad4-b823-fdb24f06ef22",
      "name": "Setup Info"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🗄️ SQL Setup - Tables\n\nRun in Supabase SQL Editor:\n\n```sql\n-- 1. Enable vector\nextension vector;\n\n-- 2. Docs table (768 dims)\nCREATE TABLE n8n_docs (\n  id bigserial PRIMARY KEY,\n  content text,\n  metadata jsonb,\n  embedding vector(768)\n);\n\n-- 3. Chat memory\nCREATE TABLE n8n_chat_history (\n  id bigserial PRIMARY KEY,\n  session_id text NOT NULL,\n  message jsonb NOT NULL\n);\n\n-- 4. Indexes\nCREATE INDEX ON n8n_docs \n  USING ivfflat (embedding vector_cosine_ops);\nCREATE INDEX ON n8n_chat_history (session_id);\n```",
        "height": 592,
        "width": 528,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -2400,
        -1136
      ],
      "id": "fc12f528-ad9b-49d2-b288-fbe7fa5ad8b2",
      "name": "SQL Setup - Tables"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔍 SQL Setup - Search Function\n\n⚠️ REQUIRED - Copy to Supabase SQL Editor:\n\n```sql\nCREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION match_documents (\n  query_embedding vector(768),\n  match_count int DEFAULT null,\n  filter jsonb DEFAULT '{}'\n) RETURNS TABLE (\n  id bigint,\n  content text,\n  metadata jsonb,\n  similarity float\n)\nLANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $$\nBEGIN\n  RETURN QUERY\n  SELECT\n    id,\n    content,\n    metadata,\n    1 - (n8n_docs.embedding <=> query_embedding) as similarity\n  FROM n8n_docs\n  WHERE metadata @> filter\n  ORDER BY n8n_docs.embedding <=> query_embedding\n  LIMIT match_count;\nEND;\n$$;\n```\n\n⚠️ This function is REQUIRED for the workflow to work!",
        "height": 640,
        "width": 480,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1800,
        -1136
      ],
      "id": "sql-function-note",
      "name": "SQL Setup - Function"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 💬 Chat Usage\n\n1. Copy webhook URL from \"When chat message received\" node\n\n2. Call via API:\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \"YOUR_WEBHOOK_URL\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"message\": \"How to setup webhook?\"}'\n```\n\n3. The AI will search docs and answer with sources!",
        "height": 416,
        "color": 7
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -2592,
        176
      ],
      "id": "68824aaa-0b1e-4ca2-9812-70c3d1c1b440",
      "name": "Chat Usage"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📥 First Setup\n\n1. Run SQL commands (see SQL Setup note)\n\n2. Create credentials in n8n:\n   - GitHub API\n   - Google Gemini\n   - Supabase\n   - PostgreSQL\n\n3. Connect credentials to nodes\n\n4. Activate \"Schedule Trigger\" workflow FIRST to populate vector store\n\n5. Then activate Chat workflow",
        "height": 576,
        "color": 5
      },
